  "current_unit": {
    "page_no": 19,
    "unit_id": "p19_g01",
    "unit_mode": "semantic_group",
    "slot_count": 3,
    "source_text": "大流行病對我們2020年財務表現的主要影響是對新業務銷售的影響，原因在於我們眾多市場的遏制傳播措施限制\n了面對面的銷售活動，尤其是在2020年上半年。儘管2020年的新業務價值27.65億美元較2019年減少了33%，我\n們迅速採用了新的數碼工具，並且外出限制的普遍放寬支持了銷售勢頭的恢復。友邦保險中國業務為2020年本集",
    "current_translation": "The primary impact of the pandemic on our 2020 financial performance was on new business sales, as containment measures in many of our markets restricted face-to-face sales activities, particularly in the first half of 2020. Although VONB of US$2,765 million in 2020 was 33% lower than in 2019, we rapidly adopted new digital tools and the general easing of movement restrictions supported a recovery in sales momentum. AIA China was the largest contributor to the Group's VONB in 2020 and was our first reporting segment to show a recovery in sales momentum, as the region progressively eased strict lockdowns from March 2020. Excluding Mainland Chinese visitor sales to Hong Kong, which remained at low levels, VONB across our other segments recovered strongly in the second half, growing 23% compared to the first half..."
  },
